how It feels *

00:24.420 --> 00:28.550
* The air is warm,
my heart is cold *

00:28.590 --> 00:30.251
* And I'll never know...

00:30.290 --> 00:32.053
Sorry for the wait,
Mr. Bordelon.

00:32.100 --> 00:35.149
Oh, no.
No problem.

00:38.300 --> 00:40.165
Sign here.

00:40.200 --> 00:42.839
Initial here,
here, and here.

00:42.870 --> 00:46.101
- And don't forget the date.
- All right.

00:54.380 --> 00:56.280
Here you go.

00:56.320 --> 00:58.208
It might take two or three
business days to process,

00:58.250 --> 01:00.150
but now you got access
to the $100,000

01:00.190 --> 01:01.782
your sister deposited
in the farm account.

01:01.820 --> 01:04.152
The debit cards
for Nova Bordelon
and Charley Bordelon-West

01:04.190 --> 01:05.623
will be mailed out
to you.

01:05.660 --> 01:08.823
Your sister already...

01:08.860 --> 01:10.418
completed the sole
proprietor forms.

01:10.470 --> 01:12.688
She even set up the tax ID
and filled out the DBA.

01:12.740 --> 01:15.163
She's pretty
on top of it.

01:15.200 --> 01:17.737
Charley's
somethin' else.

01:17.770 --> 01:21.103
( mutters )

01:21.140 --> 01:22.448
Hey, Ralph Angel!

01:22.480 --> 01:24.641
- Hey, ain't nothin'.
- What's up?

01:24.680 --> 01:26.113
Man, you in the
flower business now?

01:26.150 --> 01:28.311
Oh, man,
this is for Miss April.

01:28.350 --> 01:31.217
- What?
- I ain't paid not one
overdraft fee in years.

01:31.250 --> 01:33.753
- I like that.
- Charley still in L.A.?

01:33.790 --> 01:36.452
Yeah, she got me
handlin' the farm.

01:36.490 --> 01:39.891
She left you in charge?
I didn't mean disrespect.

01:39.930 --> 01:43.229
She just had me
look into some farm managers
while she was gone

01:43.270 --> 01:44.897
and everybody's all booked up
this late in the season.

01:44.930 --> 01:47.330
Well, I guess
it's on me then, ain't it?

01:47.370 --> 01:49.531
- All right.
- I'm buying seed cane
from the Ag Station today.

01:49.570 --> 01:51.902
Oh, that's good.
That means you guys
already got the farm

01:51.940 --> 01:54.135
registered
with the state.

01:54.180 --> 01:56.148
- Yeah, I got it.
- All right.

01:56.180 --> 01:58.341
Hey. If the Ag
is sold out,

01:58.380 --> 02:01.349
I can call over to LSU,
check on their supply.

02:01.380 --> 02:03.416
I got it, Remy,
I appreciate it.

02:03.450 --> 02:06.578
Remy:
Okay. Hey, just holler
if you need anything.

02:09.830 --> 02:13.254
( phone beeps,
line rings )

02:13.300 --> 02:16.224
- Hey.
- Hey, Charley,
what's goin' on?

02:16.270 --> 02:18.397
Just running errands.

02:18.430 --> 02:20.694
The bank called,
said you're all set up.

02:20.740 --> 02:22.503
They don't waste
no time, huh?

02:22.540 --> 02:24.303
I was calling
to tell you that.

02:24.340 --> 02:26.228
So, you're buying
seed cane now?

02:26.280 --> 02:29.670
Uh, soon.
Goin' to work,
then I gotta grab Blue.

02:29.710 --> 02:31.905
But I'm buying it today,
don't worry about that.

02:31.950 --> 02:34.771
Okay, but before
you spend a dime,

02:34.820 --> 02:37.516
make sure you ask about
the different cane varieties.

02:37.550 --> 02:40.314
Yeah, I-I'll ask.

02:40.360 --> 02:42.658
Ralph Angel, you'd tell me
if this was too much,

02:42.690 --> 02:45.284
right?

02:45.330 --> 02:48.788
I-- I need this
to go smoothly.

02:48.830 --> 02:50.718
I know.

02:50.770 --> 02:52.738
It will, I promise.

02:52.770 --> 02:56.706
Hey, I gotta go.
I'ma talk to you later,
all right?

02:56.740 --> 02:57.707
( beeps )

03:27.340 --> 03:29.262
( knocking on door)

03:32.280 --> 03:34.578
So, what brings you
in today, Mrs. West?

03:34.610 --> 03:36.976
Um, you just had your last
Pap smear six months ago.

03:37.010 --> 03:39.319
I know.

03:39.350 --> 03:41.648
But I need you
to test for everything.

03:42.750 --> 03:44.786
Okay.

03:49.360 --> 03:51.885
( theme music playing )

03:51.930 --> 03:56.321
* Dreams never die,
take flight, as the
world turns *

