04:19.390 --> 04:22.382
Yeah, I say that we focus
our efforts on Nike
and McDonald's

04:22.430 --> 04:24.352
before they drop
Davis's ad.

04:24.390 --> 04:25.823
If TAG Heuer wants out,
let them go.

04:25.860 --> 04:27.498
That's not
your call, MIrIam.

04:27.530 --> 04:30.363
We want luxury.
Mercedes Benz,
Calvin Klein...

04:30.400 --> 04:33.767
We didn't work for_ all these
years for DaVIs to just hawk
fast food and sneakers.

04:33.800 --> 04:36.360
- Let's give it some more time--
- Call Jochen at Rolex.

04:36.410 --> 04:38.799
Tell them Davis
wants to sever with TAG.

04:38.840 --> 04:42.799
Suggest five over five years
instead of TAG's five over two.

04:46.880 --> 04:50.384
"GQ" is likely to drop Davis
from their "_Men of the Year"
Issue.

04:50.420 --> 04:54.049
Look, I can make a call.
Our PR firms have worked
together in the past.

04:54.090 --> 04:56.456
Don't.
This is actually
for the better.

04:56.490 --> 04:59.459
A "GQ" spread
would reinforce
some playboy image.

04:59.500 --> 05:02.526
Nathan, have any of the other
players spoken to the press
since the suspension?

05:02.570 --> 05:04.390
I haven't been able
to get ahold of the Wives.

05:04.430 --> 05:06.967
Word is that
they have teamed up.

05:07.000 --> 05:10.731
Mounting a joint defense
to repeal the league's
decision.

05:10.770 --> 05:13.409
Without_ us.
Interesting.

05:13.440 --> 05:16.978
I can reach out to Coach Ross
and Andrew, have them make a
public statement--

05:17.010 --> 05:20.719
No need. Davis and I
are meeting with them
this afternoon.

05:22.050 --> 05:24.689
Charley, look...

05:24.720 --> 05:28.417
_ I know that this
IS personal for you,
but I am Davis's agent--

05:28.460 --> 05:30.985
This is personal.

05:31.030 --> 05:33.726
I built
those relationships.

05:35.530 --> 05:36.895
That's all for now.

05:36.930 --> 05:39.091
Nathan,
follow up with Cliff
at Mercedes Benz,

05:39.130 --> 05:40.768
and Miriam?

05:40.800 --> 05:42.904
We'll talk later.

05:44.010 --> 05:45.898
Okay.

05:54.150 --> 05:55.845
( line rings )

05:55.880 --> 05:57.711
- Hey, Nova.
- Hey.

05:57.750 --> 05:59.718
Did you get my messages?

05:59.760 --> 06:03.127
Yes, I got your messages.
But I'm not spying on Rah
for you, Charley.

06:03.160 --> 06:04.627
It's not spying.

06:04.660 --> 06:06.890
Ralph Angel was
supposed to call and
reserve the seed cane.

06:06.930 --> 06:09.125
He's buying it today.
I just need you
to check in on him.

06:09.160 --> 06:12.493
That task don't
need no hand holdin'
and you know it.

06:12.540 --> 06:14.496
Plus, I told y'all,
the farm was your project--

06:14.540 --> 06:18.135
No, no, what you said
was you would commit to it
for the season--

06:18.170 --> 06:20.604
And I meant it.
But I'm on a story.

06:20.640 --> 06:22.608
Charley:
Wait, I thought you were
taking time off from work?

06:22.650 --> 06:24.470
We all gotta get back
to livin', Charley.

06:24.510 --> 06:26.819
Listen,
you put Rah in charge,
so let him handle it,

06:26.850 --> 06:30.479
or you can come back
to St. Jo and look over
his shoulder yourself, okay?

06:30.520 --> 06:33.387
IfI could be there,
I would.

06:34.920 --> 06:36.478
( sighs )

06:36.530 --> 06:39.749
I'll do what I can.
But I ain't on no hook.

06:39.800 --> 06:41.688
Thank you.

06:42.800 --> 06:44.529
Davis:
Hey.

06:50.610 --> 06:53.579
I was afraid you and Micah
were never coming back.

06:58.710 --> 07:01.042
Charley, baby...

07:01.080 --> 07:03.947
What's her name?

07:03.990 --> 07:06.208
- Who?
- The prostitute.

07:06.250 --> 07:09.287
What's her name,
Davis?

07:13.160 --> 07:16.527
She goes by "Goldie."

07:16.570 --> 07:18.925
"Goldie"?

07:18.970 --> 07:22.462
So, you have me out here
looking crazy over a ho
named Goldie?

07:22.510 --> 07:24.933
Baby, I messed up.

07:24.970 --> 07:26.528
I messed up.

07:26.580 --> 07:29.469
Charley,
I don't know
what to do.

07:29.510 --> 07:31.569
The car is here
to take me to school.

07:33.520 --> 07:36.148
- I can go by myself.
- No, no, baby,
I'll go with you.

07:36.180 --> 07:38.717
Just give me a minute.

07:44.290 --> 07:46.258
I'll do my job
as your manager,

07:46.290 --> 07:49.453
but don't expect me
to play the dutiful wife
holding your hand.

07:56.610 --> 07:58.498
( sizzling, crackling )

07:58.540 --> 08:01.008
- ( music playing )
- ( snaps fingers )

08:03.080 --> 08:07.847
So, you give any thought
to pushing your schedule?

08:07.880 --> 08:10.280
Do you hear that?

08:10.320 --> 08:12.618
- What? I don't hear nothin'.
- Exactly.

08:12.660 --> 08:15.254
'Cause ain't nobody
in this house

08:15.290 --> 08:17.850
except for me and you.

08:17.890 --> 08:19.596
( laughing )

08:19.630 --> 08:22.895
Just ask if you can
go back next week.

08:22.930 --> 08:24.625
Chre,

08:24.670 --> 08:26.763
I can't be pushin'
my schedule around.

08:26.800 --> 08:29.735
I took time off
for the funeral.

08:29.770 --> 08:34.207
If I take any more
time off I'm gonna
have to find me a new job.

08:34.240 --> 08:36.606
Well, you could...

08:36.650 --> 08:37.742
work the farm
with Ralph Angel.

08:37.780 --> 08:40.772
- ( chuckles )
- No, you could.

08:40.820 --> 08:43.288
Come on, Baton Rouge
don't need you.

08:43.320 --> 08:46.289
Baby,
it's only two weeks,
all right?

08:46.320 --> 08:49.756
Now, what about my
goin'-away dinner?

08:49.790 --> 08:52.020
You know,
your pie is so good,

08:52.060 --> 08:55.689
it make my toes curl.

08:55.730 --> 08:59.222
But that_ain't
the only thing that
make my toes curl.

08:59.270 --> 09:01.636
( moans )

09:01.670 --> 09:04.559
- You right.
- Mm-hmm.

09:04.610 --> 09:07.636
We got so much work
to do around here

09:07.680 --> 09:10.308
- 'fore you got to leave.
- Mm-hmm.

09:10.350 --> 09:12.773
So, I tell you what,
why don't you...

09:12.820 --> 09:15.709
clean all this up.

09:15.750 --> 09:19.083
And I'ma go get...
dressed for work.

09:20.990 --> 09:23.584
Now, wait a minute.

09:23.630 --> 09:25.325
Vi?

09:25.360 --> 09:27.191
Vi?

09:27.230 --> 09:28.993
Girl, you play too much.

09:31.370 --> 09:33.588
( phone chimes )

09:33.640 --> 09:35.665
Are you still texting
with Stella?

09:35.700 --> 09:39.704
You're gonna see her
in five seconds.

09:39.740 --> 09:41.674
- What is so important--
- Mom! Stop!

09:41.710 --> 09:43.678
Well, what are you texting?
It must be really important.

09:43.710 --> 09:46.713
- It was very important.
- Oh, okay.

09:46.750 --> 09:48.718
- Wait, Micah.
- Yeah?

09:48.750 --> 09:50.843
Your dad and I, we...

09:52.290 --> 09:54.349
we wanted...

09:54.390 --> 09:57.257
Are you guys
getting a divorce?

09:59.330 --> 10:02.219
I don't know.

10:02.260 --> 10:05.798
But I want you
to prepare yourself.

10:08.440 --> 10:10.761
You're gonna hear
some things--

10:10.810 --> 10:13.108
online, the news,
just out there--

10:13.140 --> 10:14.778
ugly things about him.

10:14.810 --> 10:16.277
That stuff
doesn't matter to me.

10:16.310 --> 10:18.403
But it matters.

10:18.450 --> 10:21.271
Don't let
the houses or the_ cars
or the way we live

10:21.320 --> 10:23.845
have you thinking
otherwise, Micah.

10:23.890 --> 10:27.712
Society's quick
to demonize men
like your father.

10:27.760 --> 10:29.250
Black men?

10:29.290 --> 10:31.679
Yes, Micah. Black men.

10:35.760 --> 10:38.820
I just want you
to be careful, okay?

10:40.070 --> 10:42.732
- Woman: Micah! Micah!
- Micah: Thanks.

10:42.770 --> 10:44.931
You call me
if you need to, okay?

10:44.970 --> 10:46.437
Okay.

10:46.470 --> 10:49.075
- I'm good.
- Woman: Micah! Micah! Micah!

10:49.110 --> 10:50.407
Man:
Yo, Micah!

10:50.450 --> 10:52.406
Photographers:
Micah, right here!

10:52.450 --> 10:54.771
Mom, I just--

10:54.820 --> 10:56.117
( squeals )

10:57.920 --> 11:00.684
- ( squeals )
- I missed you.

11:00.720 --> 11:03.780
- I missed you.
- Micah: I missed you more.

11:03.830 --> 11:06.082
( photographers shouting )

11:06.130 --> 11:07.791
Just--

11:13.070 --> 11:15.334
( rattles, squeaks )

11:20.110 --> 11:23.773
15 to 30 for carrying
an 8-ball, ya heard me?

11:23.810 --> 11:26.347
I coulda killed somebody
and got less time.

11:26.380 --> 11:29.213
Crazy thing is,
I ain't even had
that much weight on me,

11:29.250 --> 11:31.787
but they said I did,
and since I got priors,

11:31.820 --> 11:35.358
ADA say if I take the plea
I'm looking at eight years.

11:35.390 --> 11:36.982
Three on good behavior.

11:37.030 --> 11:39.453
I wasn't trying to take
none of that, you heard me?

11:39.490 --> 11:42.391
But then they set my behind
in that cell for a whole year--

11:42.430 --> 11:44.318
When did you go
to NOLA Parish Jail?

11:44.370 --> 11:46.838
Them people
ain't waste no time,
it was right away.

11:46.870 --> 11:48.792
I was 17 when I went.

11:48.840 --> 11:51.809
They put me in max
and there wasn't no bail.

11:51.840 --> 11:54.479
They got me
on probation hold.

11:54.510 --> 11:57.047
Man, after sitting in there,
a year, I just took the plea.

11:58.880 --> 12:00.814
That life tough,
you hear me?

12:00.850 --> 12:03.512
You got cellies
putting their hands on you.

12:03.550 --> 12:05.518
I mean, they can
throw you in isolation,

12:05.550 --> 12:09.828
but then have the C05
hold your meals.

12:09.860 --> 12:11.851
Man, I ain't never
even wanna think on it.

12:11.890 --> 12:16.259
Truth is,
I don't wanna talk
about my situation.

12:18.870 --> 12:22.909
My brother did time, too,
I know it's hard.

12:22.940 --> 12:24.828
- Yeah?
- ( phone buzzes )

12:24.870 --> 12:28.271
- Give me a minute, hear?
- All right, no problem.

12:32.880 --> 12:35.348
( phone beeps,
line rings )

12:37.420 --> 12:39.911
Hey, Calvin.
I'm working.
What's up?

12:39.960 --> 12:42.383
Your friend's kid brother,
the one in lockup.

12:42.420 --> 12:44.388
Too Sweet, yes.
What about him?

12:44.430 --> 12:46.921
He's in
County Medical.

12:46.960 --> 12:48.996
He got hurt
real bad.

12:49.030 --> 12:50.566
Oh, no.

12:50.600 --> 12:52.966
I just thought
you'd wanna know.

12:54.200 --> 12:56.259
Any chance you could
meet me at the hospital?

12:56.300 --> 12:58.063
In about an hour?

13:00.180 --> 13:02.569
Why isn't Too Sweet
at the Orleans Inﬁrmary?

13:02.610 --> 13:05.443
There's overcrowding.
They send low security
inmates here.

13:05.480 --> 13:08.916
This is
a closed-off area,
only guards have access.

13:08.950 --> 13:11.089
Anybody say
what happened?

13:11.120 --> 13:15.181
- The OC said he fell.
- You can't possibly
believe that.

13:28.940 --> 13:31.158
You gonna be okay?

13:31.210 --> 13:33.929
* Let me give it
a moment *

13:34.940 --> 13:37.204
* Oh-oh-oh-hh

13:38.950 --> 13:41.942
* Just to sink in

13:44.490 --> 13:47.357
* Just to sink in

13:52.290 --> 13:56.863
* 'Cause I really pushed
the boat out *

13:56.900 --> 14:00.961
* This time

14:01.000 --> 14:04.265
* Now I'm sinkin'...

14:04.310 --> 14:07.006
* Fast

14:07.040 --> 14:08.598
* Now I'm sinkin'...

14:08.640 --> 14:10.870
* Down...

14:14.980 --> 14:17.517
In You, Lord,
I have taken refuge.

14:17.550 --> 14:19.950
Let me never be
put to shame.

14:19.990 --> 14:24.359
Keep me free from the trap
that is set for me.

14:24.390 --> 14:26.950
Therefore
You are my refuge.

14:27.000 --> 14:31.266
Into Your hands,
I commit my spirit.

14:31.300 --> 14:35.930
Deliver me, Lord,
Thy faithful God.

14:40.540 --> 14:43.976
* Let me give it
a second *

14:44.010 --> 14:48.379
* A second

14:48.420 --> 14:51.878
* Bite of the cherry

14:54.060 --> 14:57.029
* Bite of the cherry

15:01.960 --> 15:04.929
- ( clicks )
- * 'Cause I really
pushed you away *

15:04.970 --> 15:08.189
* Away, away.

15:22.990 --> 15:24.548
- Hey, slow down, man.
- Hey.

15:24.590 --> 15:26.342
You acting like you
like this job.

15:26.390 --> 15:29.587
My bad, Melvin.
Just want to get these
pallets unloaded.

15:29.620 --> 15:32.180
If I finish this,
Earl might let me
duck out early.

15:32.230 --> 15:34.619
- What you gotta do?
- Buy some seed cane.

15:34.660 --> 15:36.423
You farm?

15:36.460 --> 15:40.294
Yeah. My pops
just left me and
my sisters some land.

15:40.340 --> 15:42.968
- He just passed away.
- Oh, shit, man.

15:43.010 --> 15:45.069
- Hey, I'm sorry
for your loss.
- It's all good.

15:45.110 --> 15:49.206
Hey, you know,
my cousin farms, too.
Sugar cane, out in Jackson.

15:49.240 --> 15:51.572
They 'bout to shut it down.
They can't afford
the upkeep.

15:51.610 --> 15:53.714
He's selling and
giving away everything.

15:53.750 --> 15:56.378
Hey, look, look.
Why don't you roll out,
man? I got this.

15:56.420 --> 15:58.741
- Word?
- Yeah, yeah, go ahead.

15:58.790 --> 16:00.382
Won't take
but a few hours.

16:00.420 --> 16:02.217
Look, man,
it's nothin'.
I got It.

16:02.260 --> 16:05.081
- Ah, man. Holler at ya.
- All right.

16:06.160 --> 16:08.219
Our hands are tied
on this.

16:08.260 --> 16:12.492
It's just a
statement, Andrew.

16:12.530 --> 16:16.739
I hate to say it,
but with all the player
misconduct going on,

16:16.770 --> 16:19.603
I'm not surprised
at the league's decision.

16:19.640 --> 16:23.246
And frankly, Charley,
your meltdown on the court

16:23.280 --> 16:25.077
only brought us
more attention.

16:25.110 --> 16:26.668
Andrew...

16:26.710 --> 16:27.745
careful.

16:27.780 --> 16:31.511
An indefinite suspension
is a flat-out overreach.

16:33.690 --> 16:36.011
What are you even
talking about here?

16:36.060 --> 16:38.085
We're talking
about rape.

16:38.130 --> 16:40.496
I didn't rape anyone.

16:40.530 --> 16:44.261
Without the presence
of legal counsel,

16:44.300 --> 16:46.461
let's be mindful
of that word.

16:49.200 --> 16:51.361
Believe me,
the team is on your side.

16:51.410 --> 16:55.528
We simply have to see
where the chips fall.

16:58.080 --> 17:02.176
That's not
good enough.

17:02.220 --> 17:03.778
I need to get
to a meeting.

